<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-430-539  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 430 539.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDGE on andamp; about ATandamp;T  July 30, 1990 v5 n105 p16(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EDGE Publishing 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Telephones: Lanier to sell business telephone operations toTeleco.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Teleco Inc. (acquisitions and mergers)Lanier Worldwide Inc. (acquisitions and mergers).andO;Topic:     AcquisitionTelephone SystemsTelecommunications Services.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>TELEPHONES: LANIER TO SELL BUSINESS TELEPHONE OPERATIONS TO TELECOandM;Teleco Inc. of Greenville, SC, has signed a letter of intent to purchase thebusiness telephone operation of Lanier Worldwide Inc.andM;The business-telephone operation is part of Lanier's Voice Products Division.andO;&quot;The agreement represents a good strategic move for both companies,&quot; saidTony Amason, executive vice president and general manager of the Lanierdivision.andM;&quot;Although business telephones are not central to Lanier's future strategy, wehave established a substantial market presence that offers valuable potentialto a telecommunications specialist such as Teleco.&quot;andM;&quot;This acquisition will further solidify Teleco's strong market position as itmoves into the 90s,&quot; said Bill Rogers, president and founder of theGreenville company.andM;Amason said Lanier will work closely with Teleco during the transition toensure continuity for its dealers and customers in providing quality sales,service and support.andP;  &quot;We are committed to maintaining a high level ofservice and support for our customers,&quot; he said.andM;Lanier Voice Products division is part of Lanier Worldwide, a $1 billion,Atlanta-based company that is a wholly-owned subsidiary of Harris Corp.andM;Teleco, which was founded in Greenville in 1981, is a nationwide supplier oftelecommunications systems and long-distance services with more than 80locations.andP;  In December 1989, Teleconnect Magazine rated Teleco number one inAmerica in dealer sales, with volume in excess of $109 million.andP;  This follows1986 and 1987 rankings in Inc. magazine's top 500 list of America's fastestgrowing privately-held companies.andO;</TEXT></DOC>